   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC3765bb8024f3100583aab051d7198fd2"></a>Refitting the lubrication system
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10952"> </a>Before fitting the hoses (6), it is recommended to check the presence of the O-rings (A). Lubricate them with engine oil.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_002201727.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_001801723.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10959"> </a>If nipples (9) have been removed from the cooler, fit a washer (10) on each nipple (9) and apply recommended threadlocker
            on the cooler side threads. 
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10962"> </a>Washer sharp edge shall be facing the cooler.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10965"> </a>Start nipples (9) on oil cooler (11) and tighten them, while holding hex nuts (D), to a torque of 23 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_002301728.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10970"> </a>Use engine oil to lubricate O-rings (A) of the two oil hoses (6) and nipple threads (9).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10972"> </a>Attach the hoses to the cooler nipples (9), by finger-tightening nuts (C) fully home.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10974"> </a>Tighten nuts (C) to a torque of 18 Nm ± 5% while holding the nipple hex nuts.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_056702338.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_002401729.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10982"> </a>Check the presence of the cooler vibration dampers (12) on vehicle both sides.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10984"> </a>Start fitting oil cooler (11) on headlight support pin (B).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10986"> </a>Fit spacer (8) and start screw (7).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_002501730.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_002601731.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_002701732.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10995"> </a>Position pipes (6) in the crankcase half. Position plate (5).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e10997"> </a>Apply recommended threadlocker and tighten screw (4) to a torque of 10 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_056802339.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e11002"> </a>Tighten screw (7) to a torque of 6 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_002801733.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e11007"> </a>Close hose clip (3).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_001601721.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e11012"> </a>If previously removed, position the oil pressure switch (1) with washer (2) on the cooler and tighten sensor (1) to a torque
            of 19 Nm ± 10%. 
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e11014"> </a>Connect the oil pressure switch (1) to the main wiring.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_059503069.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_059603070.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e11022"> </a>Fill the system (<a href="77245.html#DUCc57ed0d029f510058c2bed44952c77d2">Changing engine oil and filter cartridge</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e11027"> </a>Refit the front half-fairings (<a href="77985.html#DUC1ccd37182a8810058cfc8ef6d8d608d2">Refitting the front half-fairing</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e11032"> </a>Refit the oil sump guard (<a href="78008.html#DUC69eeed302aaa10058bbcf20939ae18d2">Refitting the oil sump guard</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
